   {:e #blake3 "5dfcc1a77746b171e0665ec8d4557c0b18560c5f1ccf543271e4b105a9117e9f" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :task/t-7d5cdf07; FINAL CROSS-EPIC IMPLEMENTATION ORDER:\n\nBATCH 0 (zero deps, maximum parallelism — 7 tasks):\n  ZCM-1 (P0, guidance.rs/mod.rs): Auto-transact COF hints\n  ZCM-2 (P1, guidance.rs): Full harvest urgency formula\n  ZCM-3 (P1, session.rs): Session summary as ACP\n  ZCM-4 (P2, task.rs): Completion reward\n  TAP-1 (P1, schema.rs+task.rs): Structured task schema attrs\n  BAO-1 (P1, guidance.rs): Spec refs in ACP actions\n  RFL-1 (P1, schema.rs): Action-outcome schema attrs\n\nFILE CONFLICTS IN BATCH 0:\n  guidance.rs: ZCM-2 + BAO-1 (different functions, can serialize)\n  schema.rs: TAP-1 + RFL-1 (different attribute groups, can serialize)\n  task.rs: ZCM-4 + TAP-1 (ZCM-4=close handler, TAP-1=create handler, disjoint)\n\nBATCH 1 (deps on Batch 0):\n  TAP-2 (P1, mod.rs+task.rs): CLI stdin documents [deps: TAP-1]\n  RFL-2 (P1, main.rs): Record predictions [deps: RFL-1]\n  BAO-2 (P1, mod.rs): Remove legacy footer [deps: ZCM-1]\n\nBATCH 2:\n  RFL-3 (P1, guidance.rs+mod.rs): Classify outcomes [deps: RFL-1, RFL-2]\n  TAP-3 (P2, task.rs): Task show sections [deps: TAP-1, TAP-2]\n  BAO-3 (P2, schema.rs+mod.rs): Schema diff [0 deps, but P2]\n\nBATCH 3:\n  RFL-4 (P1, guidance.rs): Ridge regression [deps: RFL-3]\n  RFL-5 (P2, status.rs): Dashboard + preview [deps: RFL-3]\n\nBATCH 4:\n  RFL-6 (P1, harvest.rs): Harvest-time refit [deps: RFL-4]\n\nBATCH 5 (tests):\n  TEST-RFL-UNIT (P1): 12 unit tests [deps: RFL-3, RFL-4]\n  TEST-RFL-E2E (P1): 15 E2E checks [deps: all RFL]\n  TEST-ZCM-E2E (P1): 10 E2E checks [deps: ZCM-1, ZCM-2, ZCM-3]\n\nTOTAL: 4 EPICs, 18 tasks, ~50 dependency edges across all workstreams.\nCRITICAL PATH: ZCM-1 → BAO-2 (removes redundancy) AND RFL-1 → RFL-2 → RFL-3 → RFL-4 → RFL-6 (completes learning loop).; Session entity: :task/t-b4d0bdfc; Session entity: :task/t-4b755edf; Session entity: :task/t-189d6d3d; CROSS-EPIC INTERACTION AUDIT:\n\nFILE CONFLICT ANALYSIS:\n- guidance.rs: touched by RFL-3 (classify outcomes), RFL-4 (ridge regression), BAO-1 (spec refs in actions), ZCM-2 (harvest urgency). FOUR tasks on one file — need serialization or careful disjoint sections.\n- mod.rs: touched by RFL-2 (record predictions), RFL-3 (classify at start of run), BAO-2 (remove legacy footer), ZCM-1 (auto-transact COF). FOUR tasks on one file.\n- schema.rs: touched by RFL-1 (action schema), TAP-1 (task section schema). TWO tasks, disjoint sections.\n- task.rs: touched by TAP-2 (stdin parsing), TAP-3 (show sections), ZCM-4 (completion reward). THREE tasks.\n- status.rs: touched by RFL-5 (dashboard). One task, isolated.\n- harvest.rs: touched by RFL-6 (refit trigger). One task, isolated.\n- session.rs: touched by ZCM-3 (session summary). One task, isolated.\n\nHIDDEN DEPENDENCIES:\n1. BAO-2 (remove legacy footer) MUST happen AFTER ZCM-1 (auto-transact COF) because ZCM-1 uses the footer injection path. If BAO-2 removes footer for ACP commands BEFORE ZCM-1 wires auto-transact into that path, ZCM-1 loses its hook point.\n2. RFL-2 (record predictions) assumes ACP output exists. It depends on ACP being deployed, which it already is. No issue.\n3. BAO-1 (spec refs in actions) modifies compute_action_from_store() in guidance.rs. RFL-3 reads from :action/* entities which store the action text. If BAO-1 changes the action text format, RFL-3 classification might be affected. Mild coupling — task ID extraction should still work.\n\nMISSING DEPENDENCY: BAO-2 should depend on ZCM-1. Currently has 0 deps but should wait for auto-transact to be wired first.; Session entity: :task/t-e8b643db; COMPREHENSIVE RECONCILIATION — Checking every discrete insight against task coverage.\n\nFROM DOG-FOOD ASSESSMENT (7 items):\n1. braid next is killer feature → CAPTURED: Strength, no task needed. R(t) trajectory optimization mentioned as future enhancement (not tasked).\n2. Claim-close rhythm works → CAPTURED: ZCM-4 (completion reward/F(S) delta). TASKED.\n3. CRB auto-reconciliation works → CAPTURED: Cross-store reconciliation mentioned but NOT TASKED (deferred, correct — requires Stage 3 multi-store).\n4. ACP solved truncation → CAPTURED: 35 tasks implemented this session. DONE.\n5. Task title bloat → CAPTURED: TAP-1/2/3 (structured documents). TASKED.\n6. Harvest ceremony friction → CAPTURED: ZCM-1 (auto-transact COF), ZCM-2 (urgency formula). TASKED.\n7. Basin competition → CAPTURED: BAO-1 (spec refs), BAO-2 (remove footer). TASKED.\n\nFROM FIRST-PRINCIPLES ANALYSIS (3 themes):\nT1 Ceremony-Flow → CAPTURED: ZCM-1/2/3/4. TASKED.\nT2 Title-as-Prompt → CAPTURED: TAP-1/2/3. TASKED.\nT3 Footer-Body Duality → CAPTURED: BAO-1/2. TASKED.\n\nFROM RESEARCH AGENT FINDINGS:\nBasin 5-layer model → CAPTURED in observation. Direction 3 (spec-language = code-language) → BAO-1. TASKED.\nTask DECOMPOSE already exists → CAPTURED: TAP-1 leverages it. TASKED.\nHarvest urgency 75% unimplemented → CAPTURED: ZCM-2. TASKED.\nAuto-transact COF → CAPTURED: ZCM-1. TASKED.\nSession summary as ACP → CAPTURED: ZCM-3. TASKED.\nPreview mode for learned weights → CAPTURED: RFL-5. TASKED.\n\nFROM HIGHEST-LEVERAGE ADDITION:\nR(t) feedback loop → CAPTURED: RFL-1..6 + tests. TASKED.\n\nITEMS MENTIONED BUT NOT TASKED:\nA. R(t) trajectory optimization (look-ahead over N turns) — mentioned for item 1 but no task exists.\nB. Cross-store reconciliation — mentioned for item 3 but correctly deferred to Stage 3.\nC. Learned context precedence (significance accumulation on ACP context blocks) — mentioned for item 4 but no task exists.\nD. Schema diff command — BAO-3 exists but has 0 deps and might be forgotten.\nE. Legacy footer removal for non-ACP commands (eventual) — not tasked (correct — migration period).\nF. Velocity-adaptive harvest in the harvest WARNING (not urgency formula) — should_warn_on_exit() needs updating too, not just the urgency computation.; RFL TASK AUDIT — 5 issues found:\n\nISSUE 1: Missing :action/timestamp and :action/features schema attributes in RFL-1. The timestamp is needed for latency computation (RFL-3). The features vector (6 R(t) metric values) is needed for the learning algorithm (RFL-4). Without features, RFL-4 can't build the X matrix for regression. Solution: add :action/timestamp (Long, unix millis) and :action/features (String, JSON array of 6 floats) to the schema.\n\nISSUE 2: RFL-2 should be CENTRALIZED in main.rs, not scattered across command files. Recording the projected action in every command builder (status.rs, task.rs, etc.) creates N duplication points. Better: record ONCE in main.rs after run() returns, by checking if output.json contains _acp field. The exit_warn_path is already extracted before run() consumes the command.\n\nISSUE 3: RFL-4's normal equations (X^T X)^{-1} X^T y may fail when X^T X is singular (collinear features — pagerank and betweenness often correlate). Fix: ridge regression w = (X^T X + lambda*I)^{-1} X^T y where lambda=0.01. One line change that prevents all singularity crashes.\n\nISSUE 4: The 50-datapoint threshold means no learning for 2-3 sessions. Add a 'preview mode' to RFL-5 dashboard: show hypothetical learned weights even below threshold, with disclaimer. This gives immediate feedback that the system is LEARNING, even before it activates.\n\nISSUE 5: TEST-RFL-E2E missing cold-start test (first command in session has no previous recommendation) and regularization test (collinear features don't crash).\nSession entity: :task/t-809353b5; Session entity: :task/t-694ce001; Session entity: :task/t-331e0817; Session entity: :task/t-e9a08a4e" :op :assert}
